            <p>Nov. 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#47;88<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have the honor to submit<lb/> to you my report on the progress of<lb/> the Seminary classes during the months<lb/> of September and October in the<lb/> branches which I instruct.  The at&#45;<lb/>&#45;tendance during the months of<lb/> September was unavoidably interrupted<lb/> to a considerable extent by the holi&#45;<lb/>&#45;days occurring in that month.<lb/>  Otherwise the attendance and deport&#45;<lb/>&#45;ment of both classes have been very<lb/> good&#44; a certain unruliness of which<lb/> I had occasion to complain in the<lb/> case of a few pupils last year having<lb/> ceased through their having left the<lb/> institution.  The present attendants<lb/> are&#44; without an exception&#44; faithful&#44;<lb/> disposed to learn and well behaved.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The lower class has read three chap&#45;<lb/>ters of Genesis XXIII&#45;XXV with Rashi&#44;<lb/> four Psalms 50&#45;54 with careful exegetical<lb/> treatment&#44; three chapters of Joshua<lb/> I&#45;III at sight&#44; history and the rudi&#45;<lb/>&#45;ments of grammar.<lb/></p>
            <p>In the higher class the method of<lb/> instruction has been largely by lect&#45;<lb/>&#45;ures and dictation exercises&#44; the<lb/> substance of which is taken down<lb/> by the class into copy&#45;books.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have lectured on Isaiah and on the<lb/> history of the early post exilic period.<lb/>  The class has read two chapters I&#45;II<lb/>  critically and learnt the grammar<lb/> of the &#91;Hebrew&#93; and &#91;Hebrew&#93; verbs.<lb/></p>
            <p>There have been considerable ad&#45;<lb/>&#45;ditions made to the working library<lb/> of the Seminary.  Seven copies of<lb/> Talmud Babli &#91;Hebrew&#93; and three copies<lb/> of &#91;Hebrew&#93; have been bought and both<lb/> classes have been furnished with grammars&#44;<lb/> the higher class with Green&#39;s and<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>the lower class with Tregeller.<lb/></p>
            <p>The lower class&#44; at my suggestion&#44; paid<lb/> for their grammars but all the other<lb/> books mentioned were purchased<lb/> by and are the property of the<lb/> Seminary.  I remain&#44; Sir<lb/> very respectfully yours<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/> Preceptor<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>From<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">329 E. 51<hi rend="sup">st</hi> St</hi><lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            </body>
